2. His ſecond vow to praiſe God. His ſecond vow and promiſe is to praiſe God: My tongue ſhall ſing aloud of thy righteouſneſs,
Ver. 14 my mouth ſhall ſhew forth thy praiſe: But to this he was unapt, ſo long as he remained in his ſin;
Ver. 15 for praiſe is not comely in the mouth of a ſinner: And alſo unable to do without Gods ſpecial aſſiſtance, But becauſe not fit to do this, he prayes. and therefore he prayes for a capacity to do both.

