                  Nor in the heart, till contrite. No nor with the heart neither, till it be broken and contrite; broken for ſin, and contrite for meer love, that it hath offended ſo good a Father; I vowe therefore to bring thee this ſacrifice, this is inſtead of all other, inſtead of many ſacrifices;
 this thou wilt not deſpiſe, and this I will tender: The ſacrifices of God are a broken spirit;
His third vow, a contrite heart The third part, in which he prayes for the Church. a broken and a contrite heart, Thou, O God, wilt not deſpiſe.

