Heavy are the things, which we now ſuffer; ſo heavy,
 that the bread we cat, is ſoaked in tears, and the drink we drink, mingled with tears, and that not ſparingly, but in a very great meaſure;
 ſo that when we are to take our ordinary repaſt, we have more mind to wéep, than to take theſe refreſhments, for thou haſt brought us to that low condition, that our Neighbours, who were wont to ſtand in feare of us, ſtrive who ſhall trample upon us, and our enemies provoke and load us with ill words, inſult over and deride us.

